Chinese President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory message to the China Soong Ching Ling Foundation during a ceremony to commemorate the foundation's 40th anniversary in Beijing on Tuesday. Established in May 1982 and named after Soong Ching-ling, the wife of Doctor Sun Yat-sen, the Beijing-based foundation focuses on international and cross-Strait exchanges and the welfare of children and teens. Sun Yat-sen, a great national hero and patriot, was the pioneer of China's democratic revolution.